        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): preserve live tool stream order",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Fixes live WebChat ordering when a tool event timestamp is older than the assistant stream segment that introduced that tool call.\n- Threads optional `toolCallId` metadata through chat stream segment types so the renderer can keep the matching tool card after its causal assistant text while preserving ordinary timestamp ordering.\n- Adds a regression test for the delayed/live timestamp race behind #92122.\n\nFixes #92122\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/chat/build-chat-items.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.test.ui.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/test-ui.tsbuildinfo`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs ui/src/ui/chat/build-chat-items.ts ui/src/ui/chat/build-chat-items.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/chat.ts ui/src/ui/app-view-state.ts ui/src/ui/app.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: WebChat live streaming can render a tool card before the assistant text that triggered it when the tool message timestamp sorts earlier than the stream segment.\n\nReal environment tested: Local Control UI rendering/model unit tests in the OpenClaw checkout on Node 22 via repo test wrappers.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/chat/build-chat-items.test.ts` with a regression case where `streamSegments[0].toolCallId` matches a tool card whose timestamp is older than the segment.\n\nEvidence after fix: The regression asserts the rendered chat items remain `[assistant stream segment, matching tool card]` even when the tool card timestamp is earlier. I also ran the production Control UI chat-item projection directly after the patch:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"behavior\": \"live Control UI chat item projection\",\n  \"scenario\": \"tool timestamp is older than the assistant stream segment that introduced it\",\n  \"visibleOrder\": [\n    \"stream:I will inspect the file.\",\n    \"tool:call-read\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The live projection output shows the assistant stream segment before the matching tool card, and focused chat item tests passed: 34 tests in `ui/src/ui/chat/build-chat-items.test.ts`.\n\nWhat was not tested: I did not run a full live Gateway session or produce a video artifact. The broader DOM chat render and controller tests passed locally, and `chat-responsive.browser.test.ts` is skipped in this local environment.\n\n",
        "branch": "fix/92122-chat-tool-stream-order",
